{"key":"processedPost-9909753","value":{"id":9909753,"first":9909690,"last":9909898,"when":1236191108,"utime":"03/04/09 08:25 PM","content":"You don't inoculate manure or other bulk substrates with spores.&nbsp; You inoculate grains or brf cakes, and when those are fully colonized, you use them as spawn to inoculate the manure.&nbsp; That's where you went wrong.<br /><br />Next time, when your grains or brf cakes are colonized, inoculate pasteurized manure in a shallow tray with your copelandia spawn.&nbsp; Make the total substrate no thicker than 1 1/2\", and then when it's colonized, put a 1/4\" peat/verm casing layer on top.<br />RR","title":"Re: Copelandia Cyan. grow need help.","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}